directions.Direction: Wash and prep sushi rice, season with rice vinegar, salt, and sugar. add 1 cup water.
Prepare the krab topping by combining the shredded imitation crab, scallions, cream cheese, kewpie mayo, sesame oil, sriracha, eel sauce, and sesame seeds
In the rice pot, your rice and water should be seasoned and ready to cook. Layer the krab mix onto the rice gently and DO NOT STIR!!
Cook on the quick rice setting
After it finishes cooking, torch it (optional), and top with furikake, more eel sauce, avocado, and cucumber!
Serve with seaweed and enjoy :)

Name: Sushi Bake (in the rice cooker)
Description: This is for those who don't have access to an oven but still want to enjoy some sushi bake cravings... I got you!

directions.Direction: 1. Soak your shiitake mushrooms until fully rehydrated. Save the water to use for the rice, OR you can use fresh mushrooms and use a broth of choice to replace this step
Mix the ingredients for the sauce and set aside.

Prep your ingredients like dicing the carrot, broccoli, slicing the Chinese sausage, and slicing the mushrooms. ALL of these are interchangeable, so use what you got! I also like adding corn into this :)
Wash the rice thoroughly
Add in equal amounts of the mushroom soaking water, so 3/4 cups, or you can substitute with any broth.
layer the rest of the prepped ingredients on top, then add about 2 tbsp of the mixed sauce.

Press cook, and once the rice cooker finishes, leave it CLOSED for another 10 minutes. The one switch rice cookers can sometimes undercook the rice when there's lots of ingredients in the pot, so letting it sit ensures that your rice cooks fully!
Open the rice cooker and enjoy with more sauce and sliced scallions!
